<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-09-25T16:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-09-25T16:44:00-05:00" n="533" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d533">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/24512:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-25T21:00:00-00:44">September
                                    25, 1942—9 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received September 26—2:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>309. From McBride.<note n="69" xml:id="d533fn69">For correspondence
                                regarding Mr. McBride’s second mission to Liberia, see <ref target="#pg_387">pp. 387</ref> ff.</note> Reference Legation’s
                            308, September 25, 5 p.m.<note n="70" xml:id="d533fn70">
                                <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_392">p.
                                392</ref>.</note> concerning German Consul. Secretary of State
                            Simpson came to see me this evening. He stated that since our conference
                            this morning he had talked with President Barclay who had agreed to
                            proceed with expulsion of German Consul and his assistants. Matter will
                            be submitted to Cabinet next Tuesday. [McBride.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hibbard</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>